def remove_non_alphanumeric(text):
  return re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z ]', ' ', text)

def remove_extra_spaces(text):
  return re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', text)

def remove_double_quotes(text):
  return re.sub(r'"', '', text)

def remove_newlines(text):
    if isinstance(text, str):
        return text.replace('\n', ' ').replace('\r', ' ')
    return text

def extract_job_name(text_source, job_titles_keywords_lits):
    keywords = []
    title_count = dict()
    for title, keywords_list in job_titles_keywords_lits.items():
        keywords.extend(keywords_list)
        title_count[title] = 0
    keywords = list(set(keywords))

    found_keywords = set()
    for keyword in keywords:
        if re.search(r'\b' + re.escape(keyword) + r'\b', text_source, re.IGNORECASE):
            found_keywords.add(keyword)

    for title_kw in found_keywords:
        for title, keywords in job_titles_keywords_lits.items():
            if title_kw in keywords:
                title_count[title] += 1

    return max(title_count, key=title_count.get) if max(title_count.values()) > 0 else "other"

def extract_languages(text_source, languages_keywords_list):
    keywords = []
    lang_count = dict()
    for language, keywords_list in languages_keywords_list.items():
        keywords.extend(keywords_list)
        lang_count[language] = 0
    keywords = list(set(keywords))

    found_keywords = set()
    for keyword in keywords:
        if re.search(r'\b' + re.escape(keyword) + r'\b', text_source, re.IGNORECASE):
            found_keywords.add(keyword)

    for lang_kw in found_keywords:
        for langu, keywords in languages_keywords_list.items():
            if lang_kw in keywords:
                lang_count[langu] += 1

    languages = []
    for lang, count in lang_count.items():
        if count != 0:
            languages.append(lang)

    languages = list(set(languages))

    if len(languages) == 0:
        return "No found"

    return "-".join(languages)

def extract_data(text_source, dict_keywords_list):
    keywords = []
    dict_count = dict()
    for item, keywords_list in dict_keywords_list.items():
        keywords.extend(keywords_list)
        dict_count[item] = 0
    keywords = list(set(keywords))

    found_keywords = set()
    for keyword in keywords:
        if re.search(r'\b' + re.escape(keyword) + r'\b', text_source, re.IGNORECASE):
            found_keywords.add(keyword)

    for item_kw in found_keywords:
        for itemu, keywords in dict_keywords_list.items():
            if item_kw in keywords:
                dict_count[itemu] += 1

    item_list = []
    for item, count in dict_count.items():
        if count != 0:
            item_list.append(item)

    item_list = list(set(item_list))

    if len(item_list) == 0:
        return "No found"

    return "-".join(item_list)

def get_best_degree(text):
    if text == "No found":
        return "No found"

    degrees_ls = text.split("-")
    academic_degrees = ["PhD", "Masters", "Associate", "Bachelors", "Diploma", "Certificate"]

    for degree in academic_degrees:
        if degree in degrees_ls:
            return degree

    return "No found"

data['num_job_level'] = data["job_level"].apply(lambda x: 1 if x == "Mid senior" else 0)
# Mid Senior:1
# Associate:0
data['num_job_type'] = data["job_type"].apply(lambda x: 2 if x == "Onsite" else 1 if x == "Remote" else 0)

# Remote:1
# Hybrid:0
